    "privileged_info_summary": "The task uses ground truth data from CAMEO Chemicals (NOAA), a real authoritative source for hazardous materials information. Most chemical UN numbers and ERG guide numbers are correct. However, two critical errors exist in the metadata: (1) Molten sulfur (UN 2448) uses ERG Guide 133 (Flammable Solids), not 128; (2) Molten naphthalene (UN 2304) uses ERG Guide 133 (Flammable Solids), not 128. Guide 128 is for Flammable Liquids (Water-Immiscible) and does not apply to molten forms of these flammable solids. All other chemical entries (Phenol solid/molten and Phosphorus solid/molten) are correctly specified.",
